# Customizer tray & launcher — LOCKED, ask the user before ANY edit

The floating Customizer launcher + slide-out tray (positioning, theme style
matching, overlay suppression, sign-in flow) is **working and verified** as of
`ai-art-studio-191` (2026-07-04). The user has explicitly required that it not
be modified without their approval. Companion rule to
`iframe-scroll-lockdown.mdc`.

## Hard rules

1. **Before editing ANY of the locked parts below, STOP and ask the user for
   explicit approval first** — even for "small" or "obviously safe" changes,
   refactors, or drive-by cleanups.
2. Read `docs/customizer-tray-architecture.md` in full before proposing a
   change. Every non-obvious rule fixed a real production bug — especially
   the signed-in pitfall (shipped twice): signed in means ONLY
   `appai_customer.isLoggedIn === true` in localStorage. `appai_customer_id`
   presence must never count, not even as a fallback — the anonymous
   bootstrap writes it for every visitor and older versions wrote it
   without the `appai_customer` record.
3. After ANY approved change, run both verification scripts against the live
   dev store and check the pass criteria in the doc:
   `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-tray-signin.ts`,
   `npx tsx scripts/diagnose-tray-overlay.ts`.
4. **If any verification fails, revert immediately and redeploy** (Railway
   `production` push + `npx shopify app deploy -f`). Do not iterate forward
   on a broken state.

## Locked parts

- `extensions/theme-extension/assets/appai-customizer-tray.js`: the whole
  file — `visibleHeaderBottom`, `verifiedClearOfHeaderChrome`,
  `updateLauncherOffsets`, `themeOverlayOpen`, `startOverlaySuppression`,
  `isSignedIn`, `openSignInFlow`, `renderSignInPanel` (in-tray Google +
  email-OTP panel: must keep the same localStorage shape as
  `completeStorefrontLogin()`, reset `state.loading` on every `draw()`, and
  validate Google results by nonce AND `isAllowedCentralAuthOrigin` — kept
  in sync with `shared/storefront-auth.ts`), `persistLogin`,
  `startGoogleSignIn`, `renderTrayBody`, `extractTrayTheme`, settings
  parsing.
- `extensions/theme-extension/assets/appai-saved-designs-nav.js`: `init()`
  return contract and `window.__APPAI_SAVED_DESIGNS_REINIT__` — the tray
  calls it after an in-tray login so Saved Designs appears without a
  reload; it must stay idempotent (observer/listener attach once).
- `extensions/theme-extension/blocks/ai-art-embed.liquid`: the
  `#appai-tray-settings` JSON element and the tray/embed script tags.
- `client/src/pages/embed-design.tsx`: `hasStoredLoggedInIdentity()`, the
  `openSignIn=1` initial state of `showOtpLogin`, and the
  `ai-art-studio:open-sign-in` message handler.
- `extensions/theme-extension/assets/appai-art-embed.js`: the `openSignIn`
  URL-param forwarding into the iframe URL.
- `server/routes.ts`: the `/customizer-pages` App Proxy route the tray reads.
